Description: FireWall-1 4.1 with a limited-IP license allows remote attackers to cause a denial of service by sending a large number of spoofed IP packets with various source addresses to the inside interface, which floods the console with warning messages and consumes CPU resources.
clean_description: firewall-1 4.1 limited-ip license allows remote attackers cause denial service sending large number spoofed ip packets various source addresses inside interface floods console warning messages consumes cpu resources

Description: kio/usernotificationhandler.cpp in the POP3 kioslave in kdelibs 4.10.95 before 4.13.3 does not properly generate warning notifications, which allows man-in-the-middle attackers to obtain sensitive information via an invalid certificate.
clean_description: kio/usernotificationhandler.cpp pop3 kioslave kdelibs 4.10.95 4.13.3 properly generate warning notifications allows man-in-the-middle attackers obtain sensitive information invalid certificate

Description: Geary before 0.6.3 does not present the user with a warning when a TLS certificate error is detected, which makes it easier for remote attackers to conduct man-in-the-middle attacks via a crafted certificate.
clean_description: geary 0.6.3 present user warning tls certificate error detected makes easier remote attackers conduct man-in-the-middle attacks crafted certificate
